"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-04-gotta-stop-simone-biles-fumes-olympic-athletes-asked-question-21358390\", \"text\": \"USgymnast Simone Biles has called on reporters to allow athletes to 'soak up the moment' rather than asking 'what's next' after they win medals at theOlympics.  Biles has been one of the stars of this summer's Games, with the 27-year-old clinching her third gold in Paris as she took the vault title in emphatic fashion on Saturday.  The stunning victory came after Biles helped the United States to women's team gold and the all-around title, three years on fromthe dreaded'twisties' the American suffered in Tokyo which forced her to withdraw from several events.  On Monday, Biles - the most decorated US gymnast in history - will return to the Bercy Arena for the\\u00a0women's balance beam final followed by the\\u00a0women's floor exercise final, where she will be targeting yet more glory.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris Olympics 2024  Over the course of the last week,Biles' war of words with former team-mate MyKayla Skinner has hit the headlinesand the Ohio-born legend has alsobeen forced to defend her husband after he was pictured wearing one of her medals.  And this morning, an agitated Biles took to X, formerly Twitter, to blast journalists and broadcasters for repeatedly asking her and her fellow competitors exactly the same question when they win medals.  'You guys really gotta stop asking athletes what's next after they win a medal at the Olympics,' Biles wrote.  you guys really gotta stop asking athletes what\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s next after they win a medal at the Olympics  'Let us soak up the moment we have worked our whole lives for.'  'What is your next step after winning Gold medal??', one of Biles' followers jokingly asked, to which she replied: 'Babysitting the medal'.  It remains to be seen whether or not Biles will commit four more years to the sport to compete at the 2028 Summer Olympics, taking place in her native United States.  'Never say never,' Biles begrudgingly told reporters in the wake of her latest gold medal success.  'Next Olympics are at home. So you just never know.  'I am getting really old.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.    ArrowMORE:Olympics schedule and results: Keely Hodgkinson wins 800m gold after success for Team GB in the velodrome  ArrowMORE:Noah Lyles speaks out on Olympic 100m final delay after track invader is caught  ArrowMORE:Convicted rapist Steven van de Velde in tears as he's booed out of Paris Olympics  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"